path.id: Theorem (Sipser). For every deterministic Turing machine M, there is a deterministic Turing machine N such that for every input word:
1. M accepts if and only if N accepts
Slogan. We can make sure that a Turing machine always halts on inputs where finite memory is used.
Simple implementation. We can store the entire list of configurations seen so far, and always check if there is a repetition.
However, this can also be done without any extra memory cells.
